1
00:00:05,760 --> 00:00:07,840
AMY: Life with the Doctor was like this.

2
00:00:10,160 --> 00:00:11,200
(SCREAMS)

3
00:00:15,080 --> 00:00:17,480
Real life was like this.

4
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,720
-(PHONE BEEPS)
-WOMAN: It's Lens Opticians.

5
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:22,080
Just a reminder your reading glasses
are ready for collection.

6
00:00:22,160 --> 00:00:24,120
-AMY: Milk. Two months out of date.
-Bye!

7
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:26,280
Yogurt. (SHRIEKS) Don't ask.

8
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:28,480
We've run out of washing tablets.

9
00:00:29,480 --> 00:00:31,400
We have two lives.

10
00:00:31,880 --> 00:00:34,080
Real life and Doctor life.

11
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:37,440
Doesn't feel like real life
gets much of a look in.

12
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,760
What do we do?

13
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:41,120
Choose.

14
00:00:41,960 --> 00:00:43,480
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

15
00:00:47,560 --> 00:00:49,240
-Not today, though.
-No, not today.

16
00:00:49,880 --> 00:00:51,680
AMY: Every time we flew away
with the Doctor

17
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:53,120
we'd just become part of his life.

18
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:56,880
But he never stood still long enough
to become part of ours.

19
00:00:56,960 --> 00:00:58,440
Except once.

20
00:01:04,720 --> 00:01:07,200
The year of the slow invasion.

21
00:01:08,520 --> 00:01:11,440
The time the Doctor came to stay.

22
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:15,360
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

23
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:50,800
(DOORBELL CHIMING REPEATEDLY)

24
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:57,800
Dad, it's half past 6:00 in the morning.

25
00:01:57,880 --> 00:02:00,600
BRIAN: What are you doing lying around?

26
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:02,440
Haven't you seen them?

27
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:07,800
RORY: What are they?

28
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:10,560
BRIAN: Nobody knows.
But they're everywhere.

29
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:12,640
Well, where did they come from?

30
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:14,680
Wait.

31
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:20,480
Doctor!

32
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,840
Invasion of the very small cubes.

33
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:26,960
That's new.

34
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:28,920
World leaders are appealing for calm.

35
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,920
The global appearance of millions
of small cubes...

36
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:35,960
Despite official warnings, people have
been taking the cubes from the streets

37
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:37,560
into offices and homes.

38
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:39,640
-What are they?
-Where did they come from?

39
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:40,800
And why are they here?

40
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:43,600
Well, they're certainly
not random space debris.

41
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:45,440
They're too perfectly formed for that.

42
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:48,560
Are they extraterrestrial in origin?

43
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:51,240
Well you'll have to ask
a better man than me.

44
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,560
All absolutely identical.

45
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:56,320
Not a single molecule's difference
between them.

46
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:59,280
No blemishes, imperfections,
individualities.

47
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:02,800
What if they're bombs?
Billions of tiny bombs?

48
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:06,960
Or transport capsules, maybe,
with a mini-robot inside?

49
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,760
Or deadly hard drives?

50
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,960
Or alien eggs?
Or messages needing decoding?

51
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:16,320
Or they're all parts of a bigger whole.

52
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,600
Jigsaw puzzles
that need fitting together.

53
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:21,520
Very thorough, Brian.
Very, very thorough. Well done.

54
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:24,480
Stay here, watch these.
Yell if anything happens.

55
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:28,840
Doctor, is this an alien invasion?
Because that's what it feels like.

56
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:30,800
There couldn't be life forms
in every cube, could there?

57
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:33,320
I don't know.
And I really don't like not knowing.

58
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:39,120
Right! I need to use
your kitchen as a lab.

59
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:42,080
Cook up some cubes, see what happens.

60
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,920
Right. I'm due at work.

61
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,840
What? You've got a job?

62
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,320
Of course I've got a...

63
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,960
What do you think we do
when we're not with you?

64
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:51,760
I imagine mostly kissing.

65
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:54,320
I write travel articles for magazines
and Rory heals the sick.

66
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,520
My shift starts in an hour.
You don't know where my scrubs are?

67
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,440
In the lounge, where you left them.

68
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:02,920
(POLICE RADIO CHATTER, INDISTINCT)

69
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,920
MAN: Target unconfirmed. May be hostile.

70
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,400
Approaching source now.

71
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:12,560
Area will be secured in 60 seconds.
Ultimate force available.

72
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,960
Ah, the Ponds.

73
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:19,680
With their house and their jobs
and their everyday lives.

74
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:22,200
The journalist and the nurse.

75
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:24,080
-(SONIC SCREWDRIVER BUZZING)
-Long way from Leadworth.

76
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,480
We think it's been ten years.

77
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:28,880
Not for you or Earth, but for us.

78
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:31,760
Ten years older, ten years of you.

79
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:33,120
On and off.

80
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:36,120
Look at you now.

81
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:40,760
All grown up.

82
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:43,040
(LOUD CRASH)

83
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,560
(POLICE CHATTER ON RADIO)

84
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,440
-Trap One, kitchen secured.
-Trap Three, back garden secured.

85
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:58,760
There are soldiers all over my house
and I'm in my pants.

86
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:00,600
My whole life
I've dreamed of saying that.

87
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:02,320
And I miss it by being someone else.

88
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:05,400
All these muscles and they still
don't know how to knock.

89
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:07,400
Sorry about the raucous entrance.

90
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:10,480
Spike in artron energy reading
at this address.

91
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:13,320
In the light of the last 24 hours,
we had to check it out

92
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:15,600
and the dogs do love a run-out.

93
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:20,120
Hello. Kate Stewart,
Head of Scientific Research at UNIT.

94
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:21,960
And with dress sense like that...

95
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:23,760
(BEEPING)

96
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,720
...you must be the Doctor.

97
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:30,560
I hoped it'd be you.

98
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:34,360
Tell me, since when did science
run the military, Kate?

99
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:37,840
Since me. UNIT's been adapting.
Well, I dragged them along.

100
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,200
Kicking and screaming, which...

101
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:42,000
which made it sound like
more fun than it actually was.

102
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,480
What do we know about these cubes?

103
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:45,200
Far less than we need to.

104
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:47,800
We've been freighting them in
from around the world for testing.

105
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:50,440
So far we've subjected them
to temperatures of

106
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:52,160
plus and minus 200 Celsius,

107
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:54,600
simulated a water depth of five miles,

108
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:56,800
dropped one out of a helicopter
at 10,000 feet

109
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:59,120
and rolled our best tank over it.
Always intact.

110
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:01,160
That's impressive.
I don't want them to be impressive.

111
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:03,320
I want them vulnerable,
with a nice Achilles heel.

112
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:05,120
We don't know how they got here,

113
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,120
what they're made of
or why they're here.

114
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:10,480
And all around the world people are
picking them up and taking them home.

115
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:14,480
Like iPads have dropped out of the sky.
Taking them to work, taking pictures,

116
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:17,240
making films, posting them on Flickr
and YouTube.

117
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:21,040
Within three hours, the cubes had
1,000 separate Twitter accounts.

118
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:23,560
-Twitter.
-I've recommended we treat this

119
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:24,760
as a hostile incursion,

120
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:27,080
gather them all up and lock them
in a secure facility,

121
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:31,000
but that would take massive
international agreement and cooperation.

122
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:32,680
We need evidence.

123
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:36,560
The cubes arrived in plain sight,
in vast quantities, as the sun rose.

124
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:38,360
So, what does that tell us?

125
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:41,080
Maybe they wanted to be seen, noticed.

126
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:43,520
Or more than that,
they want to be observed.

127
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:45,400
So we observe them, stay with them.

128
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,880
Round the clock, watch the cubes,
day and night.

129
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:51,880
Record absolutely everything about them.
Team cube, in it together.

130
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:56,840
Four days, nothing.

131
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:59,000
Nothing.

132
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:02,040
Not a single change in any cube
anywhere in the world.

133
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:05,040
Four days and I am still in your lounge!

134
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:06,720
You were the one who wanted
to observe them.

135
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,200
Yes, I thought they'd do something,
didn't I?

136
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:10,760
Not just sit there
while everyone eats endless cereal!

137
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:13,320
You said we had to be patient.

138
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:16,560
Yes, you! You, not me.
I hate being patient.

139
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:17,920
Patience is for wimps.

140
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:22,920
I can't live like this. Don't make me.

141
00:07:23,320 --> 00:07:25,000
-I need to be busy.
-Fine!

142
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:27,800
-Be busy. We'll watch the cubes.
-Yes.

143
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,600
(LAWNMOWER HUMMING)

144
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:40,280
Ninety-eight, 99, 100. Amy!

145
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:51,080
Four million, nine hundred
and ninety-nine. Five million.

146
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:56,520
That's better. Nothing like
a bit of activity to pass the time.

147
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:58,240
How long was I gone?

148
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:00,160
Uh, about an hour.

149
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:04,400
I can't do it.

150
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:07,200
Where are you going?

151
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:10,400
Brian! You're still here.

152
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,720
-You told me to watch the cubes.
-Four days ago.

153
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,960
Doesn't time fly
when you're alone with your thoughts?

154
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,640
You can't just leave, Doctor.

155
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:20,560
Yes, of course I can.
Quick jaunt, restore sanity.

156
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:22,800
Ooh! Hey, come if you like.

157
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:24,360
They can't just go off like that.

158
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:26,320
Can't they? Can't you?
That's how it goes, isn't it?

159
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:27,480
I've got my job.

160
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:30,600
Oh, yes, Rory, the universe is awaiting
but you have a little job to go to.

161
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:32,960
It's not little. It's important to me.

162
00:08:33,040 --> 00:08:35,760
Look, what you do isn't all there is.

163
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:41,000
I never said it was.

164
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:43,280
All right. Fine.

165
00:08:43,680 --> 00:08:47,160
I'll be back soon.
Monitor the cubes, call me.

166
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:50,320
I'll have the Tardis set
to every Earth newsfeed.

167
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,240
(DOOR CLOSES)

168
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:57,080
At the end of a week of cubic
questions and theories but no answers,

169
00:08:57,160 --> 00:09:01,440
could this be the greatest stealth
marketing campaign in business history?

170
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:04,600
And if it is,
will those behind it ever come forward

171
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:06,600
and explain exactly what it's for?

172
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,480
I'm so pleased for you two.

173
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,760
It's about time you made
an honest woman of her.

174
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:15,200
-Amy, about bridesmaids.
-Mmm.

175
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:17,840
You've missed quite a few things
the last year or two.

176
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:20,000
I'm so totally there, whatever you need.

177
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:24,560
Everyone here loves you.
The nurses, the doctors.

178
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:26,520
You're a lifesaver, mate, literally.

179
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,760
Well, thanks.

180
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:29,640
There are months
where we don't see you.

181
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:32,160
And we can't do without you.
I want you to go full-time.

182
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:34,320
Full-time? Blimey. Uh...

183
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,600
I said yes.

184
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:40,520
-I committed.
-And I committed to being a bridesmaid.

185
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:43,680
Months in advance.
Like I know I'm going to be here.

186
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:47,800
So, the Doctor's God knows where,
the cubes aren't doing anything at all.

187
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:50,440
Did real life just get started?

188
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,480
-I like it.
-So do I.

189
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,920
Brian's log. Day 67.

190
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,440
You can't call it that. Brian's log?

191
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:10,560
Brian's log. Day 67.

192
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:15,040
Cube was quiet all night, once again.

193
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:17,520
Cube was quiet all day.

194
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:22,080
As per previously,
no movement, no change in measurements.

195
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:24,080
End of entry.

196
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:27,880
You stay up and watch it all the time?

197
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:29,880
I film it while I'm asleep.

198
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:32,480
When I wake up, I watch the footage
on fast-forward.

199
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:35,400
I email the result to UNIT.

200
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,440
My middle name is Diligence.

201
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:40,400
Wow! I can't wait to see day 68.

202
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:44,240
Don't mock my log.
I'm doing what the Doctor asked.

203
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:49,240
(MERRY XMAS EVERYBODY
BY SLADE PLAYING ON PA)

204
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:52,320
Uh, Mr Ryan, please.

205
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:54,720
Again?

206
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,600
I'm fine, I've been done.

207
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:19,560
-What seems to be the matter?
-I'm just waiting for a prescription.

208
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:22,000
-Where does it hurt?
-I said I'm fine.

209
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:25,720
Can you tell your colleague here
that I...

210
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,080
Stop!

211
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:33,280
(MAN SCREAMING)

212
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:39,040
(PHONE RINGING)

213
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,960
Hey! Doctor, it's me. Hello.

214
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:08,880
So, the UN classified the cubes as
provisionally safe, whatever that means.

215
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:11,000
And Banksy and Damien Hirst
put out a statement

216
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,520
saying the cubes are
nothing to do with them.

217
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,640
And the cubes, well,
they're just here, still.

218
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:16,480
What's it been, nine months?

219
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:19,600
People are just taking them for granted.
Maybe we'll never know why they came.

220
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:23,040
But anyway, I got to Laura's wedding.
It was great. She's here tonight,

221
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,760
being as it's our wedding anniversary.

222
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:27,920
We thought you might have dropped by.
I left you messages.

223
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,880
I know! Happy anniversary!

224
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:34,640
Come with me and bring your husband.
(CLAPS TWICE)

225
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:39,240
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

226
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:44,040
Twenty-sixth of June, 1890.

227
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:47,960
The recently opened Savoy Hotel.
Dinner, bed and breakfast for two.

228
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:50,920
Bonjour, bonjour. Merci, Auguste.

229
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,840
You'll be back before the party is over,
they won't even notice you went.

230
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:56,480
No complications, I promise.

231
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:59,120
Oh.

232
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,400
(LAUGHING)

233
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:06,280
Bit of a shock.

234
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:10,960
Zygon ship under the Savoy,
half the staff impostors.

235
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:14,600
Still, it's all fixed now, eh?

236
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,040
MAN: Check the corridors!

237
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:18,440
I thought we were going home.

238
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:21,360
You can't miss a good wedding.
Under the bed, under the bed.

239
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:23,520
(MAN SHOUTING, HALL DOORS OPENING)

240
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,640
Shh!

241
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:26,400
-It wasn't my fault.
-It was totally your fault.

242
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:28,440
Somebody was talking
and I just said yes.

243
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:29,520
RORY: To wedding vows!

244
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:31,480
You just married Henry VIII
on our anniversary.

245
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:36,320
(SNEEZES)

246
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:39,600
Sorry.

247
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:41,720
(ALL CHEERING)

248
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:43,920
(WHOOPS)

249
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:47,440
How long were they away?

250
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:50,200
I don't know what
you're talking about, Brian.

251
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:53,880
Because they're wearing
totally different clothes from earlier.

252
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,360
Seven weeks.

253
00:13:56,760 --> 00:13:58,280
I got side-tracked.

254
00:13:58,360 --> 00:13:59,720
A lot.

255
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:03,560
What happened to the other people
who travel with you?

256
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:06,640
Uh...

257
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:08,920
Some left me.

258
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:12,000
Some got left behind.

259
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,400
And some,

260
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:18,000
not many, but...

261
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:22,320
some died.

262
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:28,360
Not them. Not them, Brian.

263
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,400
Never them.

264
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:42,480
Can I...stay here

265
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:47,640
with you and Rory for a bit?
Keep an eye on the cubes.

266
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:50,360
However long that takes?

267
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:53,080
I thought it would drive you mad.

268
00:14:53,160 --> 00:14:55,760
No. No, no.
I mean, I'll be better at it this time.

269
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:57,720
I._..

270
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:01,240
Miss you.

271
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:07,640
Brian's log. Day 361.

272
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:12,360
8:50 p.m., no movement.

273
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:19,120
And I am cream-crackered.

274
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:36,080
I sent you out to sell as many cubes
as you could in 24 hours.

275
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:39,400
And look at you, you've made a right
hash of it, haven't you?

276
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,560
Well Craig, you're fired.

277
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:45,960
If I had a restaurant,
this'd be all I'd serve.

278
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:48,160
Yeah, right. You running a restaurant.

279
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:49,680
I've run restaurants.

280
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:52,240
Who do you think invented
the Yorkshire pudding?

281
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:53,920
(CHUCKLING)

282
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:55,680
You didn't.

283
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:57,120
Pudding yet savoury.

284
00:15:57,640 --> 00:15:58,680
Sound familiar?

285
00:16:03,040 --> 00:16:04,200
(CUBE BUZZES)

286
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:12,120
(CLEARS THROAT)

287
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:24,960
(GASPS)

288
00:16:28,920 --> 00:16:30,000
Do it again.

289
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:39,080
Good job, mister.

290
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:42,720
Civilisations saved. Surfaces wiped.

291
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:45,360
What more could any woman ask for?
I mean it.

292
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:49,520
-Where's the Doctor?
-On the Wii again.

293
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:51,040
-Oh.
-I'm going for a bath.

294
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:07,520
(GRUNTING)

295
00:17:08,040 --> 00:17:12,320
Oh, that's second set, Doctor! (LAUGHS)

296
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:15,200
Oh, if Fred Perry could see me now, eh?

297
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:17,160
He'd probably ask for his shorts back.

298
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,880
(WARBLING)

299
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:28,480
Ah!

300
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:52,720
Third set decider, come on, then.

301
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:58,040
Out of the way, dear, I'm trying to...

302
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:04,000
Whatever you are,

303
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:08,080
this planet, these people,
are precious to me,

304
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:12,040
and I will defend them
to my last breath.

305
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,480
Is that all you can do? Hover?

306
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,800
I had a metal dog could do that.

307
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:26,000
Ooh! Ooh, that's clever. What's that?

308
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:28,760
Whoa!

309
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:48,040
-Ooh, you really have woken up.
-RORY: Doctor!

310
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:51,640
Hi, uh, the cube in there,
it just opened.

311
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:53,360
The cube upstairs just spiked me
and took my pulse.

312
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:57,080
(LAUGHS) Really? Mine fired laser bolts
and now it's surfing the net!

313
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:58,440
You're never going to believe this.

314
00:18:58,840 --> 00:19:00,360
-My cube just moved.
-(MOBILE RINGING)

315
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:01,960
-It rattled.
-(DOCTOR CHUCKLING)

316
00:19:02,280 --> 00:19:03,640
-Hello?
-Rory, mate.

317
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:04,920
I'm desperate for help.

318
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,320
People are saying
they're being attacked by the cubes.

319
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,800
It's going to be a long night.

320
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:10,720
RORY: Okay, I'm on my way.

321
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:16,320
I have to get to work,
they need all the help they can get.

322
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:17,600
Let me come, help out.

323
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:21,360
Take-your-dad-to-work night, brilliant.
Okay, you going to be all right here?

324
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:24,080
-Keep away from the cubes.
-Right.

325
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:27,200
What are you grinning about?

326
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:29,480
We're wanted at the Tower of London.

327
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:37,240
Every cube across the whole world
activated at the same moment.

328
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:38,440
Now we're in business.

329
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:41,000
You sent me a message
to my psychic paper.

330
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:42,640
You know what? I'm almost impressed.

331
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:44,360
Secret base beneath the Tower?

332
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:45,720
Hope we're not here
because we know too much.

333
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:49,720
Yes, I've got officers trained
in beheading. Also, ravens of death.

334
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:51,520
I like her.

335
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:55,320
(ANNOUNCEMENT ABOUT CUBES
ON PA, INDISTINCT)

336
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:59,280
There are 50 being monitored
and more coming in all the time.

337
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,120
I don't know how useful it is.

338
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:04,880
Every cube is behaving individually,
there's no meaningful pattern.

339
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:07,480
Some respond to proximity.

340
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:09,920
Some create mood swings.

341
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,240
(WOMAN SOBBING)

342
00:20:11,320 --> 00:20:13,400
AMY: What's this one?
KATE: Try the door.

343
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,600
(CHICKEN DANCE PLAYING)

344
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:19,720
On a loop.

345
00:20:23,080 --> 00:20:25,720
-This is the latest.
-DOCTOR: Oh, dear.

346
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:30,320
Systems breach at the Pentagon, China,
every African nation, the Middle East.

347
00:20:30,760 --> 00:20:32,560
KATE: I've got governments
screaming for explanations

348
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:35,760
and no idea what to tell them.
I'm lost, Doctor.

349
00:20:36,280 --> 00:20:37,560
We all are.

350
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:39,840
Don't despair, Kate. Your dad never did.

351
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:47,640
Kate Stewart, heading up UNIT,
changing the way they work.

352
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:49,360
How could you not be?

353
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:50,840
Why did you drop Lethbridge?

354
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,920
I didn't want any favours.

355
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,560
Though he guided me, even to the end.

356
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:57,920
"Science leads," he always told me.

357
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,720
Said he'd learnt that
from an old friend.

358
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:03,520
We don't let him down.
We don't let this planet down.

359
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:04,640
(MONITOR BEEPING)

360
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:08,880
They've stopped.

361
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:11,240
The cubes, across the world,
they just shut down.

362
00:21:11,320 --> 00:21:13,680
Active for 47 minutes
and then they just die?

363
00:21:13,760 --> 00:21:16,080
-Not dead, dormant maybe.
-Then why shut down?

364
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:17,480
I don't know.

365
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:21,160
I don't know, I need to think.
I need some air.

366
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:24,240
Who has an underground base?

367
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:26,360
Terrible ventilation.

368
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,800
The moment they arrived,
I should have made sure

369
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:35,960
they were collected and burned.
That is what I should have done.

370
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:38,080
How? Nobody would have listened.

371
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:43,520
You're thinking of stopping, aren't you?
You and Rory.

372
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:45,400
No. I mean, we haven't made a decision.

373
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:47,400
But you're considering it.

374
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:50,840
Maybe. I don't know, we don't know.

375
00:21:51,640 --> 00:21:53,560
Well, our lives have changed so much.

376
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:59,160
Well, there was a time, there were years
when I couldn't live without you.

377
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:00,600
Um...

378
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:03,840
When just the whole everyday thing
would drive me crazy.

379
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:06,680
But since you dropped us back here,
since you gave us this house,

380
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:08,360
you know, we've built a life.

381
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:10,480
I don't know if I can have both.

382
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:13,440
-Why?
-Because they pull at each other.

383
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:16,040
Because they pull at me

384
00:22:16,120 --> 00:22:18,160
and because the travelling is starting
to feel like running away.

385
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:19,560
-That's not what it is.
-Oh, come on.

386
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:21,400
Look at you - four days in the lounge
and you go crazy.

387
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:22,760
I'm not running away.

388
00:22:23,320 --> 00:22:27,600
But this is one corner
of one country and one continent

389
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:29,720
on one planet
that's a corner of a galaxy

390
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:31,360
that's a corner of a universe

391
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:34,160
that is forever growing and shrinking
and creating and destroying

392
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:36,400
and never remaining the same
for a single millisecond

393
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:39,400
and there is so much,
so much to see, Amy.

394
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:43,400
Because it goes so fast.

395
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:48,640
I'm not running away from things,
I am running to them,

396
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:51,560
before they flare and fade forever.

397
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:58,040
It's all right.
Our lives won't run the same.

398
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:00,600
They can't.

399
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:04,480
One day, soon, maybe,

400
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:07,040
you'll stop.

401
00:23:09,080 --> 00:23:10,680
I've known for a while.

402
00:23:10,760 --> 00:23:12,960
Then why do you keep coming back for us?

403
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:18,680
Because you were the first.

404
00:23:18,760 --> 00:23:20,800
The first face this face saw.

405
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:24,680
And you were seared onto my hearts,

406
00:23:24,760 --> 00:23:26,200
Amelia Pond.

407
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:28,760
You always will be.

408
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:34,640
I'm running to you and Rory,
before you...

409
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:38,200
fade from me.

410
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:45,080
Don't be nice to me.

411
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:48,280
-I don't want you to be nice to me.
-Yeah, you do, Pond.

412
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:50,160
And you always get what you want.

413
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:54,440
-They got what they wanted.
-What? Who did?

414
00:23:54,520 --> 00:23:56,680
The cubes, that's why they stopped.
Come on.

415
00:23:57,320 --> 00:23:58,520
Kate!

416
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:00,640
Before they shut down,
they scanned everything,

417
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:03,320
from your medical limits to your
military response patterns.

418
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:08,360
They made a complete assessment
of planet Earth and its inhabitants.

419
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:10,440
That's what the surge of activity was.

420
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:12,240
Problem with the power?

421
00:24:12,760 --> 00:24:15,400
Not possible, we've got backups.

422
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:17,480
Hmm.

423
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,680
Doctor? Look!

424
00:24:27,120 --> 00:24:28,640
DOCTOR: What?
KATE: Why do they all say seven?

425
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:31,960
Seven. Seven, what's important about
seven? Seven wonders of the world.

426
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:36,680
Seven streams of the river Ota.
Seven sides of a cube.

427
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:40,240
-A cube has six sides.
-Not if you count the inside.

428
00:24:48,520 --> 00:24:49,720
It has to be a countdown.

429
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:52,200
-Not in minutes.
-Why would it be minutes, Kate?

430
00:24:52,280 --> 00:24:54,320
We have to get humanity
away from those cubes.

431
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:56,360
God knows what they'll do
if they hit zero.

432
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:57,960
Get the information out any way you can.

433
00:24:58,040 --> 00:25:00,360
News channels, websites,
radio, text messages.

434
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:02,280
People have to know
that the cubes are dangerous.

435
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:05,360
Okay, but why is this starting now?
I mean, the cubes arrived months ago.

436
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:07,680
-Why wait this long?
-Because they're clever.

437
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:09,280
Allow people
enough time to collect them,

438
00:25:09,360 --> 00:25:11,200
take them into their homes,
their lives.

439
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:14,720
Humans, the great early adopters.
And then wham!

440
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:16,680
Profile every inch of Earth's existence.

441
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:18,040
Discover how best to attack us.

442
00:25:18,120 --> 00:25:20,080
Get that information
out any way you can, go.

443
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:22,840
Right. Every cube was activated.

444
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:25,920
There must be signals,
energy fluctuations on a colossal scale.

445
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:28,320
There must be some trace.

446
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:31,600
There can't not be.
We need to think of all the variables.

447
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:33,800
All the possibilities.
Okay, go, go, go, go!

448
00:25:33,880 --> 00:25:36,200
NEWSREADER:
This is a national security alert.

449
00:25:36,280 --> 00:25:38,480
The Government advises
that members of the public

450
00:25:38,560 --> 00:25:40,520
dispose of all cubes.

451
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:44,520
If there are cubes inside your house,
remove them immediately.

452
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:48,720
Get them out of the building.
Just away from here, as far as you can.

453
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:51,080
And get back here before it hits zero.

454
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:56,600
Dad, could you go
and get me box of tape for dressings?

455
00:25:56,680 --> 00:25:58,120
It's just the cupboard
around the corner.

456
00:25:58,200 --> 00:25:59,600
Yes, boss.

457
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:14,680
Sorry. Excuse me.

458
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:17,720
I'm looking for the supplies cupboard.

459
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:22,440
I said I'm looking
for the supplies cupboard.

460
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,520
-Look, have you seen my dad?
-No, sorry.

461
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:45,600
Hey. Dad. Hey!

462
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,040
Hey!

463
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:53,440
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

464
00:26:59,880 --> 00:27:01,200
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

465
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:32,080
AMY: Doctor, please,
you don't have to do this.

466
00:27:32,280 --> 00:27:34,240
She's right.
You don't have to be in there.

467
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:36,960
-We can do this remotely.
-Remotely isn't my style.

468
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:38,920
See you after.

469
00:28:31,080 --> 00:28:32,760
Geronimo.

470
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:36,720
What's happening?

471
00:28:44,040 --> 00:28:45,600
Well, what's in there?

472
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:47,880
There is nothing in here.

473
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:49,840
AMY: Um, well, that's good.

474
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:52,360
You know, it's not bombs,
it's not aliens.

475
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:54,360
Why? Why is there nothing inside?

476
00:28:54,440 --> 00:28:56,720
Why? It doesn't make any sense.

477
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:01,160
Glasses, is it the same?

478
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:03,720
-Is it the same all around the world?
-KATE: They're empty.

479
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:05,160
We're safe, right?

480
00:29:05,240 --> 00:29:07,120
No, no, no, we are very far from safe.

481
00:29:07,200 --> 00:29:09,120
All along, every action
has been deliberate.

482
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:11,480
Why draw attention to the cubes
if they don't contain anything?

483
00:29:11,560 --> 00:29:13,000
Doctor, look.

484
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:16,040
GLASSES: They're CCTV feeds
from across the world

485
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:17,560
that are showing the same.

486
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:19,200
People are dying.

487
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:21,280
What? They can't be dying.
How? How are they dying?

488
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:24,560
KATE: I want information
on how people are being affected.

489
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:26,840
Uh, the cubes brought
people close together.

490
00:29:26,920 --> 00:29:28,800
They opened and then... (SCREAMS)

491
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:32,400
Doctor, what's the matter?

492
00:29:32,480 --> 00:29:34,280
-(RAPID BEEPING)
-I don't know!

493
00:29:34,360 --> 00:29:36,560
Hospitals are logging a global surge
in heart failures,

494
00:29:36,640 --> 00:29:37,840
-cardiac arrests.
-That's it. Ah!

495
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:40,040
Ah! Ah! Only one heart.

496
00:29:40,120 --> 00:29:41,600
-Other one's not working.
-AMY: Okay.

497
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:43,040
I'm going to get you to the hospital.

498
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:46,600
No, no, no, no, no, no!
Turn around, turn around, turn around.

499
00:29:46,880 --> 00:29:49,560
Tell me, show me.
Ten seconds after the cubes opened,

500
00:29:49,640 --> 00:29:51,880
show me the patterns
in their electrical currents.

501
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:54,000
-(COMPUTER BEEPING)
-See?

502
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:56,160
-No!
-Yes, the power cut.

503
00:29:56,240 --> 00:29:58,160
They suck the power and then...
(SCREAMS)

504
00:29:58,240 --> 00:30:00,960
They're signal boxes.
People leaning ni, wham,

505
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:04,240
pure electrical surge out of the cube
targeted at the nearest human heart.

506
00:30:04,320 --> 00:30:06,840
The heart, an organ powered
by electrical current.

507
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:10,400
Short-circuited. How to destroy
a human? Go for the heart.

508
00:30:10,480 --> 00:30:13,160
Ow! Crikey Moses!

509
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:15,600
Doctor, the scan that you set running.

510
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:17,600
The transmitter locations,
it's found them.

511
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:21,120
Oh, look at them all,
pulsing, bold as brass.

512
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:22,960
Seven of them all across the world.

513
00:30:24,080 --> 00:30:26,840
Ow! Seven stations, seven minutes.
Why is that important?

514
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:30,600
Ah! Ow, ow!

515
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:33,000
How do you people manage one heart?

516
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:34,560
It is pitiful!

517
00:30:35,720 --> 00:30:38,360
The wormhole bridging two dimensions.

518
00:30:38,640 --> 00:30:40,440
Seven of them etched onto this planet,

519
00:30:40,520 --> 00:30:43,360
but-but-but where's the closest one?
Glasses, zoom in.

520
00:30:46,760 --> 00:30:48,720
That's the hospital where Rory works.

521
00:30:57,840 --> 00:30:59,760
Dad. Dad!

522
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:04,800
Just get away from him.

523
00:31:07,520 --> 00:31:10,440
-How many deaths have been recorded?
-We don't know.

524
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:13,040
We think it could
be a third of the population.

525
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:15,920
Kate, I have to find the wormhole.

526
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:18,920
But the attacks could still happen.
Tell the world.

527
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:20,400
Tell them how to deal with this.

528
00:31:20,480 --> 00:31:22,320
The world needs
your leadership right now.

529
00:31:22,400 --> 00:31:24,600
-I'll do my best.
-Of course you will. Good luck.

530
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:26,120
Kate... (GROANS)

531
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:30,520
Okay, how long are you
going to last with only one heart?

532
00:31:30,600 --> 00:31:34,280
Not much longer.
I need to locate the wormhole portal.

533
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:35,880
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER BUZZING)

534
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:38,360
Hello, hello.

535
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:40,480
Ah, hello.

536
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:44,120
You are giving off
some very strange signals.

537
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:47,360
Oh, my God!

538
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:51,000
Outlier droid monitoring everything.

539
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:53,840
If I shut her down, I can...

540
00:31:54,560 --> 00:31:56,120
(ELECTRONIC WARBLING)

541
00:31:57,560 --> 00:31:58,760
It's all right. It's all right.

542
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,920
Ah! I can't, Amy.

543
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,720
I can't do it. I need both hearts.

544
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:04,320
(GROANING)

545
00:32:09,240 --> 00:32:10,280
All right.

546
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:12,400
-Desperate measures.
-What?

547
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:16,480
No! No, no, no. That won't work.
I'm a time lord. Ah, hey! (SCREAMS)

548
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:18,840
-No. No...
-All right, clear!

549
00:32:18,920 --> 00:32:20,320
(GROANS)

550
00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:24,320
Ooh!

551
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:27,800
Welcome back, leftie!

552
00:32:27,880 --> 00:32:31,320
Whoa-ho! Two hearts. Whoo!

553
00:32:32,320 --> 00:32:33,800
Back in the game.

554
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:36,640
Never do that to me again.

555
00:32:39,360 --> 00:32:40,400
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

556
00:32:41,240 --> 00:32:44,240
Oh, portal to another
dimension in a goods Lift?

557
00:32:45,360 --> 00:32:49,240
The energy signals converge here.
Does seem a bit cramped, though.

558
00:33:07,880 --> 00:33:10,080
Through the looking glass, Amelia.

559
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:17,440
AMY: Where are we?
DOCTOR: We're in orbit.

560
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:19,800
-One dimension to the left.
-Rory!

561
00:33:21,360 --> 00:33:24,080
Saborian smelling salts.
Outlawed in seven galaxies.

562
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:25,720
Whoa-ho!

563
00:33:25,800 --> 00:33:28,320
Whoa! What kind of
a weapon do you call that?

564
00:33:28,800 --> 00:33:30,880
-Get them out of here. You two, now!
-What are you gonna do?

565
00:33:30,960 --> 00:33:34,240
Absolutely no idea.
Get him through the portal.

566
00:33:35,440 --> 00:33:36,680
Whoa!

567
00:33:37,280 --> 00:33:39,240
So many of them

568
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:41,320
crawling the planet,

569
00:33:41,760 --> 00:33:44,680
seeping into every corner.

570
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:01,440
It's not possible.

571
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:06,080
I thought the Shakri were a myth.

572
00:34:06,560 --> 00:34:09,600
A myth to keep the
young of Gallifrey in their place.

573
00:34:09,680 --> 00:34:15,640
The Shakri exist in all of time,
and none.

574
00:34:15,720 --> 00:34:19,480
We travel alone and together.

575
00:34:20,200 --> 00:34:21,560
The seven.

576
00:34:21,640 --> 00:34:25,800
The Shakri craft connected to Earth
through seven portals in seven minutes.

577
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:27,240
Ah, but why?

578
00:34:27,680 --> 00:34:31,320
Serving the word of the Tally.

579
00:34:32,680 --> 00:34:35,400
Why the cubes? Why Earth?

580
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:38,520
Not Earth, humanity.

581
00:34:38,720 --> 00:34:43,600
The Shakri will halt the human plague
before the spread.

582
00:34:43,960 --> 00:34:46,960
Erase humanity
before it colonises space.

583
00:34:51,880 --> 00:34:54,480
We thought the cubes were an invasion,

584
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:56,640
the start of war.

585
00:34:57,800 --> 00:35:01,200
The human contagion only

586
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:04,600
must be eliminated.

587
00:35:06,240 --> 00:35:07,520
Who are you calling a contagion?

588
00:35:07,600 --> 00:35:09,480
DOCTOR: Oi, didn't I tell you two to go?

589
00:35:09,560 --> 00:35:12,640
-You should have learnt by now.
-Yeah, and what is this Tally, anyway?

590
00:35:12,960 --> 00:35:15,920
Some people call it Judgment Day
or the Reckoning.

591
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:19,200
-Don't you know?
-I've never wanted to find out.

592
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:22,600
Before the closure there is the Tally.

593
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:25,720
The Shakri serves the Tally.

594
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:28,240
DOCTOR: The pest controllers
of the universe.

595
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:30,120
That's how the tales went, isn't it?

596
00:35:30,200 --> 00:35:33,560
Wow! That's some seriously
weird bedtime story.

597
00:35:33,640 --> 00:35:36,600
You can talk.
Wolf in your grandmother's nightdress?

598
00:35:36,680 --> 00:35:39,160
So, here you are,

599
00:35:39,240 --> 00:35:42,480
depositing slug pellets
all over the Earth,

600
00:35:43,520 --> 00:35:46,920
made attractive
so humans will collect them,

601
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:50,320
hoping to find something
beautiful inside.

602
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:52,160
Because that's what they are.

603
00:35:52,240 --> 00:35:55,760
Not pests or plague, creatures of hope.

604
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:58,440
Forever building and reaching.
Making mistakes, of course.

605
00:35:58,520 --> 00:36:01,360
Every life form does.
But... But they learn.

606
00:36:01,880 --> 00:36:04,600
And they strive for greater
and they achieve it.

607
00:36:09,200 --> 00:36:10,960
You want a tally?

608
00:36:11,960 --> 00:36:14,080
Put their achievements
against their failings

609
00:36:14,160 --> 00:36:15,960
through the whole of time.

610
00:36:16,680 --> 00:36:19,840
I will back humanity
against the Shakri every time.

611
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:25,400
(CHUCKLES) The Tally must be met.

612
00:36:26,760 --> 00:36:29,720
The second wave will be released.

613
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:30,960
AMY: What does that mean?

614
00:36:31,680 --> 00:36:34,720
It's going to release more cubes
to kill more people.

615
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:37,480
Tell the Secretary-General
it's not just hospitals and equipment,

616
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:40,160
it's people.
Our best hope now is each other.

617
00:36:40,440 --> 00:36:45,160
The human plague, raiding and fighting.

618
00:36:46,080 --> 00:36:48,600
And when cornered,

619
00:36:48,680 --> 00:36:52,360
the rage to destroy.

620
00:36:52,840 --> 00:36:54,360
You are too late, Doctor.

621
00:36:54,840 --> 00:36:58,760
The Tally shall be met.

622
00:37:00,080 --> 00:37:02,000
-He's gone.
-He was never really here.

623
00:37:02,080 --> 00:37:03,920
It's just the ship's
automated interface,

624
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:06,440
like a talking propaganda poster.

625
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:09,640
I can stop the second wave.

626
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:12,160
I can disconnect all the Shakri craft
from their portals,

627
00:37:12,240 --> 00:37:15,360
leave them drifting in the dark space.
Ah, but all those people

628
00:37:15,440 --> 00:37:17,800
who were near the cubes,
so many of them will have died.

629
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:20,760
-I restarted one of your hearts.
-You'd need mass defibrillation.

630
00:37:20,840 --> 00:37:22,760
Of course. Ah. Beautiful. But...

631
00:37:22,840 --> 00:37:25,640
Pond, Ponds! We are going to go
one better than that.

632
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:28,760
The Shakri used the cubes
to turn people's hearts off.

633
00:37:28,840 --> 00:37:31,800
Bingo! We're going to use them
to turn them back on again.

634
00:37:31,880 --> 00:37:34,440
-Will that work?
-Ah, creatures of hope.

635
00:37:34,520 --> 00:37:35,960
Has to.

636
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:43,880
Thirty seconds.

637
00:37:43,960 --> 00:37:46,760
Don't let me down, cubes.
You're working for me now.

638
00:37:50,280 --> 00:37:52,000
Oh, dear! All those cubes.

639
00:37:52,080 --> 00:37:54,040
There's going to be
a terrible wave of energy

640
00:37:54,120 --> 00:37:56,080
ricocheting around here any second.

641
00:37:57,280 --> 00:37:58,600
Run!

642
00:37:58,680 --> 00:38:00,120
I'm going to miss this.

643
00:38:02,760 --> 00:38:04,040
(SCREAMING)

644
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:07,280
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

645
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:15,280
NEWSREADER: Emergency hospitals
and field units

646
00:38:15,360 --> 00:38:17,920
are working at full capacity
around the world,

647
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:20,760
as millions of survivors
of cardiac arrest

648
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:22,360
are nursed back to health

649
00:38:22,440 --> 00:38:24,960
after an unprecedented
night across the globe.

650
00:38:28,760 --> 00:38:30,000
KATE: You, uh...

651
00:38:30,520 --> 00:38:33,080
You really are
as remarkable as Dad said.

652
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:37,920
-Thank you.
-My!

653
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:39,800
A kiss from a Lethbridge-Stewart.

654
00:38:40,160 --> 00:38:43,440
That is new. (LAUGHS)
Oh! I'm late for dinner.

655
00:38:45,200 --> 00:38:46,280
Ah!

656
00:38:56,080 --> 00:38:57,360
(LAUGHING)

657
00:38:57,880 --> 00:39:01,240
Hmm. Forgive me.
I'd better get going. Things to do.

658
00:39:01,480 --> 00:39:04,440
Worlds to save, swings to...

659
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:06,840
swing on.

660
00:39:13,120 --> 00:39:16,040
Look, I know you both have lives here.

661
00:39:16,120 --> 00:39:21,480
Beautiful, messy lives. That is what
makes you so fabulously human.

662
00:39:21,880 --> 00:39:23,720
You don't want to give them up.

663
00:39:24,360 --> 00:39:25,440
I understand.

664
00:39:25,520 --> 00:39:27,840
Actually, it's you
they can't give up, Doctor.

665
00:39:30,640 --> 00:39:32,400
And I don't think they should.

666
00:39:33,080 --> 00:39:34,560
Go with him.

667
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:37,720
Go save every world you can find.

668
00:39:37,800 --> 00:39:39,960
Who else has that chance?

669
00:39:40,640 --> 00:39:42,400
Life will still be here.

670
00:39:42,840 --> 00:39:46,240
-You could come, Brian.
-Somebody's got to water the plants.

671
00:39:48,120 --> 00:39:49,920
Just bring them back safe.

672
00:39:50,880 --> 00:39:53,320
AMY: So that was
the year of the slow invasion,

673
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:56,160
when the Earth got cubed
and the Doctor came to stay.

674
00:39:56,320 --> 00:40:00,600
It was also when we realised something
the Shakri never understood,

675
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:02,960
what cubed actually means.

676
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:05,360
The power of three.

677
00:40:17,640 --> 00:40:19,640
GRAYLE: You don't believe
that statues can move.

678
00:40:20,080 --> 00:40:21,480
(CHUCKLES) And you're right,
they can't.

679
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:23,520
When you're looking.

680
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:25,080
DOCTOR: New York is policed by Angels.

681
00:40:25,160 --> 00:40:27,760
Every time you try to escape,
you get zapped back in time.

682
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:29,280
The city that never sleeps.

683
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:32,520
The Angels will come
and I think they're coming for you.

684
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:36,040
Displacing someone back in time
creates time energy.

685
00:40:36,120 --> 00:40:38,440
And that is what the Angels feed on.

686
00:40:40,920 --> 00:40:42,480
What the hell are you doing?

687
00:40:43,520 --> 00:40:45,120
-Any ideas?
-Run!

